    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 9000 Pro Sleeper After 05/01/1997, and 9800 Model After 07/01/1997 -
        DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>The Blend-Air heating and air conditioning system is a combination unit (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602001">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Both the heater and air conditioner are housed in one unit and
            use common air ducts and blowers. The term "Blend-Air" refers to mixing or blending together of air from the
            air conditioner, heater and outside air. This provides for heating, cooling, defrosting, dehumidifying and
            ventilation in whatever combination the driver chooses to select.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1602001" figsize="full-pg">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602001A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="544px"/>
            <caption>Figure 1. Blend-Air Heating and A/C Unit</caption>
